Sentencas: Co3O4-impregnated NiO-YSZ (yttria-stabilized zirconia) is a possible electrocatalyst for direct methane electrooxidation with both high catalytic activity and the ability to mitigate coking.

Sentencas: The high activity of Co3O4-impregnated NiO-YSZ is attributed to the changes in the electronic structure and microstructure with the incorporation of nickel into the lattice of Co3O4 as observed using X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy, temperature-programmed reduction, high-resolution transmission electron microscopy, and field emission scanning electron microscopy.
